            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><w>-ññe</w><w>śmaśānike</w><w>ste</w><pc>•</pc><w>orotsana</w><w>erkenmasa</w><w>en<gap reason="plain" unit="part"/><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/></w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><w>srukoṣäṃ</w>
<w>ṣaläskema<lb corresp="#a2"/>ne</w><w>ṣekaṃñe</w><w>tākaṃ</w><pc>•</pc><w>omte</w><w>leṃ</w><w>paryāṃ</w><w>yamasträ</w><w>tu</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><w>skeṃ</w><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>āñme</w><w>srukosäṃ</w>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><w>āñme</w><w>āsta</w><w>añma</w><w>postäṃ</w><w>omte</w><w>yamasträ</w><pc><supplied>•</supplied></pc><w><supplied>se</supplied></w><w>yw<supplied>ār</supplied></w><w>śk<supplied>a</supplied>ñe</w><w>śmaśānike</w>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><w>ste</w><pc>•</pc><w>akessu</w><w>śmaśānike</w><w>ste</w><pc>•</pc><w>ente</w><w>nauṣaññana</w><w>erkenma</w><w>tatākauwa</w><w>tākaṃ</w>
<lb corresp="#a5"/><w>omteṃ</w><w>leṃ</w><w>paryāṃ</w><w>yamasträ</w><w>tune</w><w>mäsketrä</w><pc>•</pc><w>śāmñana</w><w>āsta</w><w>taiysa</w><w>kwrāṣäṃ</w><w>ṣe</w></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Auf einer großen Leichenstätte, wo man (noch) beständig die Toten hinwirft, dort macht er [scil. der Śmāśānika Mönch der mittleren Richtung] sich eine Mönchszelle.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">On a large charnel ground, where [people] (still) always throw the dead, there he [i.e. the Śmāśānika monk of the middle way] makes for himself a monk's cell.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>428</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Where on a big cemetery they may still steadily throw down the dead, there indeed he makes his monk cell, and there he stays in. There he makes himself (?) dead [people] and bones, according to his [own] wish.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>704</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>704</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wo früher eine Leichenstätte war, dort macht er [scil. der Śmāśānika-Mönch der gemäßigten Richtung] sich eine Mönchszelle.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Where there used to be a charnel ground earlier, there he [i.e. the Śmāśānika monk of the moderate way] makes for himself a monk's cell.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>428</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 txt:m-tht5592#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Where formerly a cemetery [lit. a former cemetery] may have been, there indeed he makes his monk cell, and there he stays in. In this way he sets himself on human bones and skeletons all the time.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>704</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>704</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Verso Chinese. The leaf is immediately followed by <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht5592"/>. In  <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1953"/><citedRange>352</citedRange></bibl> both leaves have been edited under the no. 559.</note></p>
         </div>
